{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"upperclass-sulfuric-coney","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Plan\n\nPure/mechanical module-size split of `src/rebar/_commands/fsck.py` (855 LOC, over the 800 soft cap; grandfathered in .github/module-size-allowlist.txt + .github/module-size-ceilings.txt with a remedy row in docs/architecture.md). Extract the cohesive `--repair`/A3-remediation cluster into a NEW sibling leaf `src/rebar/_commands/fsck_repair.py`, leaving the read-only diagnostic scan (`_scan`, `_check_snapshot`, `_has_retired_create`, `_branch_mismatch`, `_push_pending` with its own local _git closure, `_transform_json`, `fsck_cli`) in fsck.py.\n\nThe docs/architecture.md offenders remedy row already names this exact seam ('extract the repair cluster ... into a sibling fsck_repair.py, leaving the diagnostic scan + _transform_json in fsck.py') — the plan MATCHES the recorded row; no deviation, and the row is deleted on graduation.\n\nMOVE to fsck_repair.py (located by name): the orphan-disposition sets `_AUTO_RECOVER_ORPHAN_TYPES`/`_HUMAN_TRIAGE_ORPHAN_TYPES`, module-level `_git`, `_resolve_tracker_git_dir`, `_ticket_dirs`, `_active_snapshots`, `_repair_plan`, `_repair_ticket`, `_has_remote`, `_reconciler_pause`/`_reconciler_resume`/`_reconciler_in_flight`, `_repair_run`. `_ticket_dirs`+`_resolve_tracker_git_dir` move to the leaf (shared by both diagnostic + repair; moving them keeps imports one-way: fsck.py re-imports from the leaf, the leaf imports nothing from fsck.py). The leaf keeps its lazy in-function imports (compact.rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log; engine_dir + rebar_reconciler._advisory_lock) as-is.\n\nBack-compat: fsck.py re-imports (re-exports) the moved names so `fsck.<symbol>` attribute access and `from rebar._commands.fsck import <symbol>` keep resolving. `_resolve_tracker_git_dir` is load-bearing (imported by _store/gitutil.py (function-local, left untouched), _commands/fsck_recover.py, and 3 tests); `_repair_plan`/`_repair_ticket`/`_AUTO_RECOVER_ORPHAN_TYPES`/`_HUMAN_TRIAGE_ORPHAN_TYPES` are re-export-only (test_fsck_snapshot_checks.py) and carry # noqa: F401. No signature/logic changes.\n\nThis is a pure/mechanical refactor; E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing fsck test suites are the oracle.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable, in-session-verifiable)\n\n1. NEW `src/rebar/_commands/fsck_repair.py` exists with 100 <= `wc -l` <= 800, containing exactly the moved repair cluster; it is a LEAF (imports nothing from rebar._commands.fsck).\n2. `wc -l src/rebar/_commands/fsck.py` <= 800 (down from 855), and it re-exports the 5 back-compat names.\n3. fsck.py's row removed from BOTH .github/module-size-allowlist.txt and .github/module-size-ceilings.txt; its offenders remedy row removed from docs/architecture.md.\n4. `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q` passes (allowlist == computed over-cap set == ceilings keys).\n5. `python -m pytest tests/interfaces/test_e4_fsck.py tests/interfaces/store/test_fsck_snapshot_checks.py -q` and `python -m pytest tests/unit -k fsck -q` pass.\n6. `make lint` reports 'All checks passed!' (ruff check + format-check).","id":"f87a-f632-0ecd-437c","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Split fsck.py — extract the --repair cluster into fsck_repair.py to graduate off the module-size soft cap"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784397251447770001,"uuid":"1a265320-159a-49ea-962b-c90567b79608"}